### Hadith 4:609

*Narrated Ibn 'Abbas:*

When the Prophet came to Medina, he found (the Jews) fasting on the day
of 'Ashura' (i.e. 10th of Muharram). They used to say: "This is a great
day on which Allah saved Moses and drowned the folk of Pharaoh. Moses
observed the fast on this day, as a sign of gratitude to Allah." The
Prophet said, "I am closer to Moses than they." So, he observed the fast
(on that day) and ordered the Muslims to fast on it.

